            en: 'Umar رضي الله عنه set out on the long journey — from Madinah to the Levant. He had a servant with him. They had agreed to take turns on the riding animal: one would ride while the other walked, then they would switch.<br><br>People had imagined the Commander of the Faithful arriving on a great horse surrounded by a protective guard — instead he walked on scorching earth with his feet and let his servant ride the animal! People stared, barely believing what they saw!'
