            en: 'Historians narrated that Abu \'Ubayda ibn al-Jarrah رضي الله عنه said to Umar once: "O Commander of the Faithful, you do things that if others did them we would see as humiliation!" Umar رضي الله عنه smiled and replied: <b>"Had anyone other than you said this, O Abu \'Ubayda! We were once the lowliest of people and Allah honored us through Islam — whenever we seek honor through anything else, Allah humiliates us."</b><br><br>So dear child, always say this: my honor comes from my faith — not from my money, nor my clothing, nor my fame!'
